<P>&nbsp&nbsp EverMon and EverGuild both requires the use of the Hydra UniNet
Launcher application for both the installation of either the EverMon or
EverMonBeta Software, as well as the real-time version update support.</P>

<P>&nbsp&nbsp If you have not yet downloaded and installed the UniNet Launcher
software, you will need to do that first.  Click on the link below to go to
the UniNet Launcher Download Instruction page.</p>

    <ul>
    <li><a href='../uninet/l_download.htm' target=main>UniNet Launcher Download Page</a>
    </ul>

<B><U><FONT SIZE=+1>After the Launcher is Installed...</FONT></U></B><BR>

<P>&nbsp&nbsp After you have successfully installed the Launcher software,
you should find a program icon created for 'Launcher Config' under your
UniNet menu in the Start Menu as shown below :</p>

    <center><img src="launcher1.jpg" border=0 alt="Home"></center>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp Once you run the Launcher Config, the launcher application will
start, connect with the launcher update web server, and get the latest version
of the launcher application configuration file, and then show you a listing
of the different applications that may be installed with the Launcher.</p>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp Under the 'EverQuest' catagory, you should find options for
EverMon, EverMon Beta, or and EverGuild Beta.  Select the particular software
that you would like to install, and then follow the instructions to confirm
your installation request, and to create the new application Icon.</p>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp Once you have installed your selection, and have quit the
Launcher configuration application, you will find a new icon created in
addition to the 'Launcher Config' icon in the UniNet menu as shown below :</p>

    <center><img src="launcher2.jpg" border=0 alt="Home"></center>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp<b> (note: this icon demonstrates the icon created if you selected
EverMon Beta. The name of the icon will be different depending on which
software you selected to install).</b></p>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp With that, you are done.  Run the newly created application
icon to start the launcher, and run your program.  Keep in mind the very
first time you run a newly installed application, it will need to download
all of the application components from the internet, which may take a few
minutes.</p>

<p>&nbsp&nbsp If you have any other problems, questions, or comments, please go to our <a href=em_support.htm target=main>Support Page</a> for additional assistance.</p>

